        "timestamp": "2020-02-06 19:43:24.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> (1 comment)\n\nThinking out loud - probably even if there was code, in any case ABATED would have never worked as the requestId that is used to match against an in progress transactions would have almost ever matched, because of the flooding nature of ONSETs being set by DCAE with potentially thousands of those instances.   Now that we prevent the flooding with the use of Canonical* objects, we can probably get to an easier solution to this, I think ..",
